cs.SI, cs.NI, cs.DS, cs.SY, cs.IT

Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper deals with modeling and predicting the spread of information or contagions through human mobility.
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also likely as the paper discusses improving delay tolerant communication schemes.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper provides rigorous analysis for the Manhattan Random Way-point model.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper deals with controlling the spread of information or contagions.
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is relevant as the paper discusses the time it takes for all bits of information to reach all agents.
